docs for user fonts feature

check status more often, at least to check for memory allocation errors
when creating a new object.

Make sure double GC of an object isn't harmful, just in case (that is, can
I manually call the '__gc' metamethod and then let the object get GCed without
the library crashing?).  Probably have to check for null before calling the
destroy function.

